race.comment: TORONADO BOOM (4) settled near the rear last start and couldn't make an impression in the straight, finishing ninth over this trip at Cranbourne. He needed the run that day, when over a month between runs, and with only 9 days since his last start, he will be a lot sharper this time. Can win. VICTORY TUNE (8) doesn't have the strongest winning record but ran a solid race last time, finishing fourth and a length and a half away over 1000m at Cranbourne after finding the line well. Stick with him. Each way. JAHANGIR (2) showed good early speed and fought on strongly to finish second by a nose over 1100m at Werribee 3 weeks ago. Hard to beat again. REGAL SECRET (5) resumes from a spell, and usually comes to hand quickly with 2 placings from 3 starts fresh up to her name. She is worth considering for all top 4 combos, especially if the money comes for her.
